From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: local build <local@orangepi3b>
Date: Tue, 16 Jun 2026 08:25:00 +0700
Subject: [PATCH] drm/panel: raspberrypi: add OPi3B probe diagnostics

The Orange Pi 3B RK3566 DSI path can fail as an endless deferred-probe loop:

  dw-mipi-dsi-rockchip fe070000.dsi: failed to find panel or bridge: -517

That only says the DSI host is waiting for a DRM panel. It does not tell us
whether the I2C panel node probed, whether the ATTINY controller answered on
0x45, or whether the panel driver is deferring while looking for the DSI host.

Add explicit probe-stage messages so UART captures identify the real blocking
point.

Do not change display timing or MIPI DSI mode flags in this patch. The
25.979 MHz preferred mode and sync-pulse/no-HBP experiments caused wrong
colors and horizontal wrap on the tested Waveshare/Raspberry-compatible
800x480 panel. Keep the vendor driver's original 26 MHz burst/no-HBP setup
while retaining useful boot diagnostics.
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/panel/panel-raspberrypi-touchscreen.c | 12 +++++++++---
 1 file changed, 9 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/panel/panel-raspberrypi-touchscreen.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/panel/panel-raspberrypi-touchscreen.c
@@ -390,10 +390,14 @@
 
 	ts->i2c = i2c;
 
+	dev_info(dev, "OPi3B DSI panel probe start, i2c addr=0x%02x\n",
+		 i2c->addr);
+
 	ver = rpi_touchscreen_i2c_read(ts, REG_ID);
 	if (ver < 0) {
-		dev_err(dev, "Atmel I2C read failed: %d\n", ver);
-		return -ENODEV;
+		dev_err(dev, "Atmel I2C read failed at addr 0x%02x: %d\n",
+			i2c->addr, ver);
+		return ver;
 	}
 
 	switch (ver) {
@@ -404,23 +408,28 @@
 		dev_err(dev, "Unknown Atmel firmware revision: 0x%02x\n", ver);
 		return -ENODEV;
 	}
+	dev_info(dev, "Atmel firmware revision 0x%02x detected\n", ver);
 
 	/* Turn off at boot, so we can cleanly sequence powering on. */
 	rpi_touchscreen_i2c_write(ts, REG_POWERON, 0);
 
 	/* Look up the DSI host.  It needs to probe before we do. */
 	endpoint = of_graph_get_next_endpoint(dev->of_node, NULL);
-	if (!endpoint)
+	if (!endpoint) {
+		dev_err(dev, "missing DSI endpoint in panel DT node\n");
 		return -ENODEV;
+	}
 
 	dsi_host_node = of_graph_get_remote_port_parent(endpoint);
 	if (!dsi_host_node)
 		goto error;
+	dev_info(dev, "remote DSI host node is %pOF\n", dsi_host_node);
 
 	host = of_find_mipi_dsi_host_by_node(dsi_host_node);
 	of_node_put(dsi_host_node);
 	if (!host) {
 		of_node_put(endpoint);
+		dev_info(dev, "DSI host not ready, deferring panel probe\n");
 		return -EPROBE_DEFER;
 	}
 
@@ -436,6 +445,7 @@
 			PTR_ERR(ts->dsi));
 		return PTR_ERR(ts->dsi);
 	}
+	dev_info(dev, "registered DSI child device for host attach\n");
 
 	drm_panel_init(&ts->base, dev, &rpi_touchscreen_funcs,
 		       DRM_MODE_CONNECTOR_DSI);
@@ -444,6 +454,7 @@
 	 * driver's component bind function.
 	 */
 	drm_panel_add(&ts->base);
+	dev_info(dev, "DRM panel registered\n");
 
 	return 0;
 
-- 
